The conceptions of ‘occult properties’ and ‘specilic virtues' belong to that stage of speculation in which men believed that the properties of objects were distinct entities, separable, as it were, from the objects themselves, and dwelling in them. ln a still prior stage of speculation, these properties had been personitied and regarded as divine.
